    • Method Detail

      • calculateThroughput

        public static java.util.List<Throughput> calculateThroughput(double startTime,
                                             double maxTS,
                                             double thStep,
                                             java.util.List<PacketInfo> packets)
        Creates a list of throughput calculations for the specified time range, sampling window, and list of packets.
        Parameters:
        startTime - The starting time in the trace to begin throughput calculations.
        maxTS - The sampling window for each throughput point.
        thStep - The ending time in the trace for throughput calculations.
        packets - A List of packets to calculate throughput on. This method assumes that these packets are sorted by timestamp. The results of this method are undefined for an unsorted packet list.
        Returns:
        A List of Throughput objects containing the results of the calculations.
